{"lemma":"كُوَرِ","slug":"كُوَرِ","root":"ك.#.ر","root_slug":"ك-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n37360","n37361"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a type of administrative division, translated as “district” or “province”, notably instituted by the Umayyad Caliphate and hence the Emirate of Córdoba","tags":["historical"],"examples":[{"text":"وأما أرمينية فإنها كورة جليلة رسمها أرميني بن كنظر بن يافث بن نوح ومنها ترتفع الستور والزلاليُّ الرفيعة كثيرة الخصائص قصبتها دَبِيل ومن مدنها: بَدْلِيس، خِلَاط، أَرْجِيش، بَرْكَرِي، خُوَيُّ، سَلَمَاس، أُرْمِيَة، دَاخَرَّقَان، مَرَاغَة، أَهْرُ، مَرَنْد، سَِنْجَان، قالِيقَلَا، قندرية، قَلْعَة يُونِس، نورين.","english":"Concerning Armenia, it is a revered region of Armenian tradition, a son like the son of Japhet, the son of Noah, and from it hail draperies and fine rugs of lots of peculiarities the filament of which is like that of Dwin, and of its towns are: [a list of settlements follows]."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Classical Syriac ܟܘܪܐ (kōrā), from Ancient Greek χώρᾱ (khṓrā)."},"ipa":["/kuː.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37360","headword_ar":"كَوْرٌ","root":"kwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) an inf. n. used as a subst., (Msb,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwrN","text_ar":"كُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISh, T, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A turn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twist,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a turban: (ISh, T, A, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akowaArN","text_ar":"اَكْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEimaAmapu Ei$oruwna kuwrFA","text_ar":"العِمَامَةُ عِشْرُونَ كُورًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The turban is"},{"kind":"text","text":"composed of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twenty turns"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arapu","text_ar":"عَشَرَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akowaArK","text_ar":"اَكْوَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ten turns"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Increase;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"redundance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEuw*u biAll~`hi mina AlHawori baEoda Alkawori","text_ar":"نَعُوذُ بِاللّٰهِ مِنَ الحَوْرِ بَعْدَ الكَوْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We have recourse to God for preservation from decrease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defectiveness, after increase,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"redundance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) or, as it is also related,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda Alkawoni","text_ar":"بَعْدَ الكَوْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means the same: or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from return to disobedience after obedience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from return after pursuing a right course."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaworN","text_ar":"حَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","ISh","T","A"]},{"entry_id":"n37361","headword_ar":"كُورٌ","root":"kwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaworN","text_ar":"كَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel's"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saddle of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makowarN","text_ar":"مَكْوَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mukowar~N","text_ar":"مُكْوَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"and teshdeed to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TS, L:] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with its apparatus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) pronounced by many"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaworN","text_ar":"كَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is a mistake: (IAth:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akowaArN","text_ar":"اَكْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akowurN","text_ar":"اَكْوُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and (of mult., TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyraAnN","text_ar":"كِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwraAnN","text_ar":"كُورَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuw^uwrN","text_ar":"كُوُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last, says ISd, is extr. as a pl. form of a sing. such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kwr","text_ar":"كور"},{"kind":"text","text":"with an infirm letter. (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A blacksmith's fire-place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majomarap","text_ar":"مَجْمَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constructed of clay:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K: *) and also said to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which he blows his fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb, TA:) or this latter is called [only]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyrN","text_ar":"كِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, in the present art.; and S, Msb, K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kyr","text_ar":"كير"},{"kind":"text","text":":) an arabicized word. (Msb.)       -A4-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hornets',"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bees', nest;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"structure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hornets:"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~anaAbiyr","text_ar":"الزَّنَابِير"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, K [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~anaAniyr","text_ar":"الدَّنَانِير"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a mistake:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of bees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(accord. to a trad. cited in the TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akowaArN","text_ar":"اَكْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwaArapN","text_ar":"كُوَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Msb","IAth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}